main event: The witness sighted a bright, elongated object that was as bright as a mercury vapor street light while driving on Grand Bank Road and I-75 in Michigan on August 7, 1967.
interesting points: The object appeared to be an elongated, bright object that was observed for 5 minutes from a moving vehicle.
The case was not submitted until February 1968, at which point it was too late to investigate further.
The witness stated the object was as bright as a mercury vapor street light and looked like an elongated object.
The report notes that there was insufficient data to evaluate the case.
The witness described the object as a 'bright glowing type of object' that appeared to sail out of sight.
location: Grand Bank Road and I-75, Michigan
